Package: miCCI
Title: Quality-Preserving Charlson Comorbidity Index Estimation Under Diagnosis Anonymisation
Version: 0.5.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Gaetan", "Kamdje Wabo", email = "gaetan.kamdjewabo@medma.uni-heidelberg.de",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Piotr", "Sokolowski", role = "aut"),
    person("Fabian", "Siegel", role = "aut"))
Description: Five training-free computational strategies for reconstructing
    the Charlson Comorbidity Index (CCI) from truncated (anonymised)
    ICD-10-GM codes: S1 deterministic interval, S2 expected value,
    S3 multiple imputation, S4 Bayesian posterior median, and S6 a
    deterministic meta-estimator that combines S1-S4 without any
    learned parameters. Reference population frequencies are taken
    from the German Federal Statistical Office (Destatis 23131-01).
    CCI mapping based on Quan et al. (2005). The pipeline is split
    into a heavy compute stage and a fast reporting stage so that
    plots and tables can be regenerated without recomputing the
    estimates.
